This paper deals with online caching algorithms, which are typically studied in the context of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The (n, k)-companion cache model is a specific type of cache, which involves designing algorithms for efficient data retrieval and storage, making it relevant to the areas of algorithms (cs.AL) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses competitive analysis, which is a common technique in the field of computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
